A grid is a biome. A world is made up of multiple biomes.

Animals at the edge can transfer between biomes in groups.

Biome:
- Temperature, Flora
- 30*30 grid

Animal:
- have points in energy
- are either carnivore or herbivore
- can spend on:
    first
        - gestation speed
        - litter size
        - metabolism/time to eat
        - attack
        - defence
        - speed
    later:
        - chance to move to new biome
        - time to sleep
        - solitary/group
        - likelihood of biome transfer
- Actions:
    - Eat food/eat other animal
    - Mate
    - Sleep
    - Move Random

Breeding:
- each animal has a species ID and can only breed within there

